== Separation of variables ==
When the problem allows additive separation of variables, the HJE leads directly to constants of motion. For example, the time &quot;t&quot; can be separated if the Hamiltonian does not depend on time explicitly. In that case, the time derivative formula_119 in the HJE must be a constant, usually denoted (formula_120), giving the separated solution
