where formula_275 is the magnetic field magnitude in a solenoid with the effective radius formula_276, inductivity formula_277, number of windings formula_278, and an electric current magnitude formula_279 through the solenoid windings. The particle motion occurs along the figure-8 trajectory in formula_280 plane set perpendicular to the solenoid axis with arbitrary azimuth angle formula_281 due to axial symmetry of the solenoidal magnetic field.

